1
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:42,509
[indistinct chatter
in distant hallway]

2
00:01:09,536 --> 00:01:10,471
[door opens]

3
00:01:11,672 --> 00:01:13,172
[running footsteps]

4
00:01:13,239 --> 00:01:15,108
[boy] Come on.
Pass, pass. I'm open.

5
00:01:15,174 --> 00:01:17,176
[man] A little slower
in the hallway, please.

6
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:18,479
- [boy 2] You're an idiot.
- [girl] What if no one asks me?

7
00:01:18,545 --> 00:01:20,179
Like last year?

8
00:01:20,246 --> 00:01:22,081
- [boy 3] I'll get that, milady.
- [laughter]

9
00:01:22,148 --> 00:01:24,250
- [school bell ringing]
- [indistinct chatter]

10
00:01:30,824 --> 00:01:32,493
[chatter continues]

11
00:01:35,962 --> 00:01:37,163
[door opens]

12
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:40,601
[piano music playing]

13
00:01:43,537 --> 00:01:45,037
[chuckles softly]

14
00:01:45,104 --> 00:01:46,673
[girl] You didn't tell me
you played piano.

15
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:48,475
[Maren] Hey.

16
00:01:50,176 --> 00:01:52,011
You are here.
Where have you been?

17
00:01:52,078 --> 00:01:53,547
You weren't in Home Ec.
All week.

18
00:01:53,614 --> 00:01:55,449
I got to slip to work
on the yearbook.

19
00:01:55,516 --> 00:01:57,183
We missed our deadline
with Jostens.

20
00:01:57,250 --> 00:01:58,951
Oh. How's it look?

21
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:02,121
You're not gonna be in it,
by the way.

22
00:02:02,188 --> 00:02:03,990
Mr. Esser said
he reminded you three times

23
00:02:04,056 --> 00:02:06,092
- to get your picture taken.
- [plays piano]

24
00:02:08,127 --> 00:02:09,863
Hey, so my dad's doing
inventory all night,

25
00:02:09,929 --> 00:02:12,031
and Kim and Jackie
are sleeping over.

26
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:14,133
Come too.

27
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,935
[continues playing piano]

28
00:02:16,002 --> 00:02:18,037
No, my dad won't let me.

29
00:02:18,104 --> 00:02:20,374
So sneak out.
After he goes to bed.

30
00:02:21,941 --> 00:02:23,176
How would I get there?

31
00:02:24,344 --> 00:02:25,512
You're down in Southwind, right?

32
00:02:27,013 --> 00:02:28,181
You know the power lines
that go up the hill?

33
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:31,652
That's Chesapeake Road
at the top. I'm right there.

34
00:02:33,420 --> 00:02:35,121
You said you wanna make
more friends here.

35
00:02:37,891 --> 00:02:39,992
[students chattering]

36
00:02:43,229 --> 00:02:45,298
Hey. Come on, you drive.

37
00:02:45,365 --> 00:02:47,166
- [boy] Okay.
- [girl] Take care. Bye.

38
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:13,327
[men laughing and chattering]

39
00:03:17,096 --> 00:03:19,533
Hey. That was good
on the road.

40
00:03:20,801 --> 00:03:22,636
Gotta work on that parking
some more...

41
00:03:23,704 --> 00:03:24,638
but good.

42
00:03:31,979 --> 00:03:33,313
You think
it's gonna rain tonight?

43
00:03:34,982 --> 00:03:36,517
Don't think it's supposed to.

44
00:03:43,857 --> 00:03:45,124
[can pops open]

45
00:03:48,127 --> 00:03:50,330
[grunts] Got homework?

46
00:03:52,064 --> 00:03:53,266
Just reading, Dad.

47
00:03:54,434 --> 00:03:56,436
<i>The man has attempted suicide.</i>

48
00:03:57,337 --> 00:03:59,339
<i>I think he realized</i>

49
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:01,775
<i>that this scheme that
he had been involved in,</i>

50
00:04:01,842 --> 00:04:04,878
<i>about which he had
always been extremely guilty.</i>

51
00:04:04,945 --> 00:04:07,981
<i>I mean, he's... he's,
I think, the only person</i>

52
00:04:08,047 --> 00:04:13,353
<i>in this entire scheme to have
voluntarily walked out on it.</i>

53
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:16,222
<i>Some people were annoyed
with it, upset with it,</i>

54
00:04:17,658 --> 00:04:19,826
<i>and... but went along with it.
Others enjoyed it</i>

55
00:04:19,893 --> 00:04:21,929
<i>because they were making
a lot of money out of it.</i>

56
00:04:21,995 --> 00:04:26,333
<i>Dowd was the only person
who had the character...</i>

57
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:28,735
'Night, Dad.

58
00:04:28,802 --> 00:04:30,003
[man on TV]
<i>...and the moral fiber...</i>

59
00:04:30,069 --> 00:04:31,738
Yeah. Sleep good.

60
00:04:31,805 --> 00:04:33,540
[man on TV]
<i>...to walk out on this scheme</i>

61
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:35,074
<i>long before anybody
knew about it,</i>

62
00:04:35,141 --> 00:04:36,643
<i>because it disgusted him.</i>

63
00:04:36,710 --> 00:04:39,145
<i>I mean, the prospect of actually</i>

64
00:04:39,211 --> 00:04:41,180
<i>walking into
Donald Manes' office</i>

65
00:04:41,247 --> 00:04:42,583
<i>and paying him cash...</i>

66
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:01,635
[wind blowing]

67
00:05:25,425 --> 00:05:27,594
- [muffled music playing]
- [muffled chatter]

68
00:05:30,196 --> 00:05:31,732
[panting]

69
00:05:38,372 --> 00:05:39,640
Hang on. Okay.

70
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:43,777
- Hey.
- Hey.

71
00:05:46,113 --> 00:05:48,749
You got prickers all over you.
Come in.

72
00:05:51,418 --> 00:05:53,487
[indistinct chatter]

73
00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:56,790
[Kim] So you can't
spend the night?

74
00:05:57,991 --> 00:05:59,426
[Maren] Not all night.

75
00:05:59,493 --> 00:06:01,328
I should be back
by 6:00 to be safe.

76
00:06:02,562 --> 00:06:03,997
Jesus.

77
00:06:04,064 --> 00:06:06,366
I'll just head out
when you guys wanna sleep.

78
00:06:08,835 --> 00:06:10,537
So where'd you move here
from anyway?

79
00:06:11,938 --> 00:06:13,172
Eastern shore.

80
00:06:14,908 --> 00:06:16,175
Is your mom in the picture?

81
00:06:18,445 --> 00:06:20,246
Sherry says you only have a dad.

82
00:06:20,313 --> 00:06:21,682
[knock on table]

83
00:06:23,249 --> 00:06:24,851
"Cinnamon Glaze."

84
00:06:26,153 --> 00:06:27,354
We're trying to talk.

85
00:06:31,425 --> 00:06:32,759
[Sherry] Kim, give me your hand.

86
00:06:39,766 --> 00:06:41,601
[Kim] Never mind about your mom.

87
00:06:41,668 --> 00:06:43,770
It's none of my business,
anyway.

88
00:06:46,173 --> 00:06:47,841
[inhales deeply]

89
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:50,844
I don't have
any memories of her.

90
00:06:52,345 --> 00:06:53,714
Or photos even.

91
00:06:55,382 --> 00:06:57,417
My dad wouldn't
tell me anything.

92
00:07:00,687 --> 00:07:03,390
Try that.
It's called "Copper Fever."

93
00:07:05,992 --> 00:07:07,327
It's too orange.

94
00:07:16,403 --> 00:07:18,839
- [bones crunching]
- [screaming]

95
00:07:20,841 --> 00:07:21,875
Oh, my God!

96
00:07:21,942 --> 00:07:23,275
Maren, stop it!

97
00:07:23,343 --> 00:07:24,911
Stop! Stop it!

98
00:07:24,978 --> 00:07:27,147
Maren, stop! Maren, no!

99
00:07:27,214 --> 00:07:28,181
- Jackie!
- [continues screaming]

100
00:07:28,247 --> 00:07:29,449
Maren, stop!

101
00:07:30,884 --> 00:07:33,252
Jackie! Jackie, help!

102
00:07:33,987 --> 00:07:34,921
Jackie, help!

103
00:07:36,623 --> 00:07:37,991
[panting]

104
00:07:52,005 --> 00:07:54,007
[banging on door]

105
00:07:57,110 --> 00:07:58,044
You didn't.

106
00:08:01,014 --> 00:08:02,783
In the car in three minutes.

107
00:08:02,849 --> 00:08:04,718
Whatever you can take
in three minutes.

108
00:08:06,285 --> 00:08:07,420
Go!

109
00:08:08,889 --> 00:08:10,056
Shit.

110
00:08:16,363 --> 00:08:18,131
Move, Maren!

111
00:08:18,198 --> 00:08:20,467
When the cops get here,
we have to be good and gone.

112
00:08:59,272 --> 00:09:00,407
Dad?

113
00:09:02,843 --> 00:09:03,777
[sighs]

114
00:09:05,045 --> 00:09:06,079
[yawning]

115
00:09:14,788 --> 00:09:15,722
Dad?

116
00:09:25,665 --> 00:09:27,667
[breathing heavily]

117
00:10:04,504 --> 00:10:05,639
[button clicks]

118
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:10,110
[Maren's father on tape]
<i>I've got some things to say.</i>

119
00:10:10,176 --> 00:10:11,111
<i>And then...</i>

120
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:14,881
<i>I want you to make sure
this, uh...</i>

121
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:17,484
<i>this tape is good
and destroyed. Don't keep it.</i>

122
00:10:18,518 --> 00:10:19,719
<i>This has got my voice on it.</i>

123
00:10:21,154 --> 00:10:23,523
You're not going
to see me again, Maren.

124
00:10:27,193 --> 00:10:28,128
I can't...

125
00:10:31,097 --> 00:10:32,098
help you anymore.

126
00:10:32,165 --> 00:10:34,034
[Maren crying]

127
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:37,003
<i>I can't do anything else,
either.</i>

128
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:41,174
<i>Call the cops or whatever
somebody might do in my place.</i>

129
00:10:43,009 --> 00:10:45,578
<i>So I gotta leave you
to figure it out for yourself.</i>

130
00:10:46,546 --> 00:10:48,181
<i>Like your mother did.</i>

131
00:10:48,248 --> 00:10:51,017
<i>I'm sorry. You know
what I mean now.</i>

132
00:10:52,185 --> 00:10:53,853
<i>I don't know how much...</i>

133
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:57,023
<i>how much of what I'm gonna say
you'll remember.</i>

134
00:10:58,426 --> 00:11:01,094
[sighs] <i>Yeah. Never was sure.</i>

135
00:11:02,162 --> 00:11:03,964
<i>But just in case,</i>

136
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:05,165
<i>I'll tell you everything I know.</i>

137
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,935
<i>First time was
when you were three.</i>

138
00:11:13,374 --> 00:11:15,575
[indistinct talking on TV]

139
00:11:15,642 --> 00:11:17,477
[newscaster]
<i>Downey has the crowd screaming</i>

140
00:11:17,544 --> 00:11:19,279
<i>at Towson State University.</i>

141
00:11:19,347 --> 00:11:21,147
<i>The topic was
the most controversial issue</i>

142
00:11:21,214 --> 00:11:23,116
<i>on this year's Maryland ballot,</i>

143
00:11:23,183 --> 00:11:24,784
<i>the gun ban referendum.</i>

144
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:26,354
<i>The majority of those
in the audience</i>

145
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:28,221
<i>seem to be against the ban,</i>

146
00:11:28,288 --> 00:11:30,123
<i>but we found those
on both sides of the issue.</i>

147
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:31,992
[woman] <i>I think it's a good law,</i>

148
00:11:32,058 --> 00:11:33,593
<i>if she gets
guns off the streets,</i>

149
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:35,595
<i>and that's what we need most.</i>

150
00:11:35,662 --> 00:11:37,497
[man] <i>I just</i>
<i>don't think it's fair</i>

151
00:11:37,564 --> 00:11:38,898
<i>for all the innocent people
that wanna get a gun</i>

152
00:11:38,965 --> 00:11:40,800
<i>to protect themselves.</i>

153
00:11:40,867 --> 00:11:42,635
<i>Just making it easier
for criminals</i>

154
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:44,904
<i>to have them than honest people.</i>

155
00:11:44,971 --> 00:11:46,740
[man 2] <i>I don't want</i>
<i>them comin' in my living room</i>

156
00:11:46,806 --> 00:11:48,808
<i>and tell me what I can
and can't buy.</i>

157
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:50,844
<i>Y'all think if you take
the guns away from everybody,</i>

158
00:11:50,910 --> 00:11:52,779
<i>you have less shooting
with the whole nine-yards,</i>

159
00:11:52,846 --> 00:11:53,980
<i>the criminals
and the innocent people.</i>

160
00:11:58,852 --> 00:11:59,853
Hi.

161
00:12:00,421 --> 00:12:01,554
Uh...

162
00:12:03,156 --> 00:12:04,190
I need to get here.

163
00:12:06,192 --> 00:12:07,894
What's the closest
I can get by bus?

164
00:12:07,961 --> 00:12:10,864
Well, looks like Detroit Lakes.

165
00:12:14,134 --> 00:12:15,735
Three transfers.

166
00:12:15,802 --> 00:12:19,806
Frederick, Maryland,
Columbus and Minneapolis.

167
00:12:21,442 --> 00:12:23,777
One way? 83.

168
00:12:25,446 --> 00:12:26,946
How much to Columbus?

169
00:12:30,317 --> 00:12:32,118
Shouldn't you be in school?

170
00:12:33,354 --> 00:12:34,654
You'd think.

171
00:12:34,721 --> 00:12:36,556
I don't know what that means.

172
00:12:38,024 --> 00:12:39,893
Means I'm 18,
in the state of Maryland,

173
00:12:39,959 --> 00:12:41,895
and I can decide for myself
where I should be.

174
00:12:43,830 --> 00:12:47,567
I'm gonna need to see a driver's
license or a learner's permit.

175
00:12:50,236 --> 00:12:51,971
You can see a birth certificate.

176
00:12:54,974 --> 00:12:55,909
Come on.

177
00:13:05,486 --> 00:13:06,686
Just to Columbus?

178
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:08,154
It's 49.

179
00:13:09,423 --> 00:13:10,357
50.

180
00:13:14,462 --> 00:13:16,296
[passengers chattering]

181
00:13:27,941 --> 00:13:29,809
[Maren's father]
<i>I had a sitter for you then.</i>

182
00:13:31,077 --> 00:13:32,879
[chuckles] <i>Her name was Penny.</i>

183
00:13:34,214 --> 00:13:36,383
<i>When I came in,
she was on the bathroom floor.</i>

184
00:13:36,450 --> 00:13:39,752
<i>There was... so much blood.</i>

185
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,722
<i>Her face was chewed up bad,</i>

186
00:13:42,789 --> 00:13:45,258
<i>but the worst of it
was her neck.</i>

187
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,629
<i>She must've been holding you
when you started in on her.</i>

188
00:13:50,564 --> 00:13:51,865
<i>Her hands, all chewed up. I...</i>

189
00:13:51,931 --> 00:13:55,068
<i>I thought you were dead too.</i>

190
00:13:55,135 --> 00:13:56,470
<i>That somebody had done you both,</i>

191
00:13:56,537 --> 00:13:58,271
<i>but you were sleepin'.</i>

192
00:13:58,339 --> 00:14:00,707
<i>When I turned you over,
I saw the blood on your mouth.</i>

193
00:14:00,773 --> 00:14:05,078
<i>You had something in your cheek.</i>

194
00:14:05,145 --> 00:14:08,047
<i>I fished it out. It was soft,
like a wad of gum.</i>

195
00:14:08,114 --> 00:14:09,949
<i>It had a little hole in it.</i>

196
00:14:10,950 --> 00:14:12,218
<i>Where an earring would go.</i>

197
00:14:14,455 --> 00:14:16,524
<i>I remember thanking God
she hadn't been wearing any,</i>

198
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:17,757
<i>you could've choked.</i>

199
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:21,428
<i>I got the body out,</i>

200
00:14:21,495 --> 00:14:23,263
<i>I bleached the place
three times,</i>

201
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:25,198
<i>and then packed us up and left.</i>

202
00:14:25,265 --> 00:14:26,400
<i>They never found
where I put her.</i>

203
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:31,271
<i>That was the last time
I used our real last name.</i>

204
00:14:32,339 --> 00:14:34,107
<i>Now you know why.</i>

205
00:14:34,174 --> 00:14:36,709
<i>Nothin' happened
for a few years. I relaxed.</i>

206
00:14:38,077 --> 00:14:39,879
<i>You had to start school
and I thought...</i>

207
00:14:39,946 --> 00:14:41,515
<i>I thought you wouldn't
do it in public,</i>

208
00:14:41,582 --> 00:14:42,715
<i>and you didn't.</i>

209
00:14:43,584 --> 00:14:44,717
<i>But you got clever.</i>

210
00:14:45,619 --> 00:14:47,220
<i>So fucking clever.</i>

211
00:14:59,165 --> 00:15:00,266
[sighs]

212
00:15:00,334 --> 00:15:01,801
[thunder rumbling]

213
00:15:22,356 --> 00:15:24,358
[rain pattering]

214
00:15:38,805 --> 00:15:40,807
[thunder continues rumbling]

215
00:16:09,269 --> 00:16:11,438
I didn't mean to scare you.

216
00:16:12,473 --> 00:16:14,140
[breathing shakily]

217
00:16:15,476 --> 00:16:16,809
You waiting for the bus?

218
00:16:19,178 --> 00:16:21,214
Well, no, missy. I...

219
00:16:22,115 --> 00:16:23,916
I came lookin' for you.

220
00:16:27,655 --> 00:16:28,788
Do I know you?

221
00:16:30,923 --> 00:16:33,394
I guess not in the way you mean.

222
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:38,197
I smelled you.

223
00:16:38,264 --> 00:16:41,134
You probably smell me now.

224
00:16:42,268 --> 00:16:45,004
When was the last time you fed?

225
00:16:46,939 --> 00:16:48,342
[thunder rumbling]

226
00:16:51,545 --> 00:16:53,012
[sniffs]

227
00:16:53,079 --> 00:16:55,349
[Maren] Stop, stop,
stop there. Stop.

228
00:16:58,217 --> 00:17:02,288
You haven't in a long time.
[sniffs]

229
00:17:02,356 --> 00:17:03,324
I'll say...

230
00:17:05,459 --> 00:17:06,893
many months.

231
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:09,062
At least.

232
00:17:10,698 --> 00:17:12,031
You can smell that?

233
00:17:12,098 --> 00:17:14,200
[chuckles] Oh, sure.

234
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:16,437
You can...

235
00:17:16,503 --> 00:17:20,139
You can smell lots of things
if you know how.

236
00:17:20,206 --> 00:17:21,140
[sniffs]

237
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:25,446
And we just smell anyway.
[laughs]

238
00:17:26,547 --> 00:17:28,948
Whether we ate or not.

239
00:17:50,671 --> 00:17:51,605
Hmm.

240
00:17:59,546 --> 00:18:00,547
Come on, missy.

241
00:18:03,282 --> 00:18:04,217
Come on.

242
00:18:14,227 --> 00:18:15,161
Come on.

243
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:21,200
[Maren] Where are we goin'?

244
00:18:21,267 --> 00:18:24,036
Just here,
someplace dry and safe.

245
00:18:25,606 --> 00:18:26,906
I'm Sullivan.

246
00:18:28,007 --> 00:18:29,676
Friends call me Sully.

247
00:18:31,311 --> 00:18:32,245
Maren.

248
00:18:33,814 --> 00:18:35,047
Is this your house?

249
00:18:37,183 --> 00:18:38,819
Listen, Maren,

250
00:18:38,886 --> 00:18:41,154
don't worry. I'm okay.

251
00:18:42,021 --> 00:18:43,557
I got rules.

252
00:18:44,525 --> 00:18:46,025
One, number one

253
00:18:46,092 --> 00:18:49,696
is never, never, ever
eat an Eater.

254
00:18:49,763 --> 00:18:51,498
Think you can follow that too?

255
00:18:53,032 --> 00:18:54,267
All right.

256
00:18:54,334 --> 00:18:56,235
I'll fix some dinner for us.

257
00:18:58,472 --> 00:19:03,009
I smelled you from the yard,
little missy. Come on.

258
00:19:03,610 --> 00:19:04,545
This far?

259
00:19:06,045 --> 00:19:08,715
[Sully] Round the back.
We'll talk inside.

260
00:19:40,547 --> 00:19:44,585
The Sully, he found
these little Cornish hens

261
00:19:45,985 --> 00:19:47,186
in the freezer.

262
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:50,424
These hens,

263
00:19:51,758 --> 00:19:54,160
they look like
they had a good life.

264
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,101
Thought I was the only one.

265
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:05,071
Are there lots of us?

266
00:20:05,137 --> 00:20:06,373
Not lots.

267
00:20:07,139 --> 00:20:09,075
But more...

268
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:12,011
