But not like rotten.

307
00:22:50,169 --> 00:22:51,304
No.

308
00:22:54,941 --> 00:22:55,942
But close.

309
00:22:56,910 --> 00:22:58,745
More like vinegar.

310
00:23:01,048 --> 00:23:03,617
Like vinegar in the soup.

311
00:23:04,718 --> 00:23:07,354
Yeah. Yeah.

312
00:23:17,731 --> 00:23:18,965
[Maren sniffing]

313
00:23:36,516 --> 00:23:39,119
[breathing laboriously]

314
00:23:39,186 --> 00:23:41,021
- She's alive.
- [Sully] Missy.

315
00:23:41,088 --> 00:23:42,422
- We'll get help.
- Missy.

316
00:23:42,489 --> 00:23:44,191
What did you do to her?

317
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:45,525
I found her like that
this mornin'.

318
00:23:45,592 --> 00:23:47,527
You're lying. Let me by.

319
00:23:47,594 --> 00:23:50,597
Listen.
Let me bone down on this.

320
00:23:51,498 --> 00:23:52,799
Whatever you and I got,

321
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:55,035
it's gotta be fed.

322
00:23:55,102 --> 00:23:56,803
[breathing shakily]

323
00:23:58,605 --> 00:23:59,740
No. Uh...

324
00:24:01,141 --> 00:24:02,743
No, 'cause it was...

325
00:24:04,377 --> 00:24:06,813
It was years
before my last time.

326
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:09,516
[sighs]
That's because you're young.

327
00:24:11,451 --> 00:24:14,354
You're gonna need it
more and more,

328
00:24:14,421 --> 00:24:16,757
- and more and more.
- [whimpering]

329
00:24:16,823 --> 00:24:21,260
And you won't always be able
to hold yourself back.

330
00:24:21,328 --> 00:24:23,830
But if the circumstances is...

331
00:24:24,765 --> 00:24:26,466
is safe and good,

332
00:24:27,634 --> 00:24:28,702
then eat.

333
00:24:29,870 --> 00:24:31,270
It'll last a while,

334
00:24:31,338 --> 00:24:34,207
maybe it'll keep you from,

335
00:24:34,273 --> 00:24:36,777
you know,
doing something you'll regret.

336
00:24:39,012 --> 00:24:41,014
[Maren continues whimpering]

337
00:24:41,882 --> 00:24:42,816
Even more.

338
00:24:43,984 --> 00:24:45,485
Even more, missy.

339
00:24:48,755 --> 00:24:50,891
Yes, Sully found her that way.

340
00:24:51,925 --> 00:24:52,959
I followed my nose.

341
00:24:56,763 --> 00:24:59,366
I don't...
I don't kill people.

342
00:25:01,635 --> 00:25:03,537
At least I try not to.

343
00:25:06,406 --> 00:25:07,941
That leaves this.

344
00:25:10,277 --> 00:25:12,746
- And things like it.
- [sniffles]

345
00:25:20,954 --> 00:25:21,888
[sniffles]

346
00:25:24,391 --> 00:25:26,293
Can I have
a few minutes, please?

347
00:25:26,359 --> 00:25:27,594
Sure, you can.

348
00:25:31,765 --> 00:25:34,701
I don't think
it'll be a long time now.

349
00:25:34,768 --> 00:25:37,537
When the time comes,
you'll smell it.

350
00:25:40,674 --> 00:25:42,776
[woman breathing laboriously]

351
00:26:03,997 --> 00:26:05,665
[woman gagging]

352
00:26:08,068 --> 00:26:09,502
[stops breathing]

353
00:26:12,005 --> 00:26:13,440
[sniffling]

354
00:26:16,710 --> 00:26:19,145
- [soft footsteps]
- [Sully breathing heavily]

355
00:26:25,018 --> 00:26:25,952
[Sully clears throat]

356
00:26:28,622 --> 00:26:32,058
- [body being dragged]
- [Sully grunting]

357
00:26:33,493 --> 00:26:34,628
[body thuds]

358
00:26:39,367 --> 00:26:41,568
- [sniffs]
- [Sully coughing]

359
00:26:42,602 --> 00:26:45,872
[crunching and slurping]

360
00:27:00,186 --> 00:27:01,721
[Maren breathes excitedly]

361
00:27:02,756 --> 00:27:04,557
[both slurping and munching]

362
00:27:18,471 --> 00:27:19,673
[yawning]

363
00:27:37,958 --> 00:27:38,892
[groans]

364
00:27:45,433 --> 00:27:46,533
[sniffs]

365
00:27:46,599 --> 00:27:48,034
This is how I do it.

366
00:27:49,202 --> 00:27:52,605
It helps me
to remember each one.

367
00:27:52,672 --> 00:27:56,509
When I began this,
I was about your age.

368
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:01,648
Pull it.

369
00:28:02,649 --> 00:28:04,017
You won't break it.

370
00:28:07,921 --> 00:28:08,855
[chuckles]

371
00:28:10,557 --> 00:28:12,792
It's strong. [laughs]

372
00:28:12,859 --> 00:28:15,695
[Maren] Who was your first?
You remember?

373
00:28:18,565 --> 00:28:20,567
I ate my own granddad

374
00:28:22,168 --> 00:28:24,771
while they were waiting
on the undertaker.

375
00:28:26,307 --> 00:28:29,175
Did anyone find you
while you were doing it?

376
00:28:29,242 --> 00:28:30,543
My mama.

377
00:28:31,978 --> 00:28:34,247
My mama found me afterwards.

378
00:28:35,316 --> 00:28:36,549
Cleaned me up.

379
00:28:38,785 --> 00:28:42,323
She told everyone
animals got in and did it.

380
00:28:42,390 --> 00:28:45,291
But when I finally ran off,

381
00:28:46,593 --> 00:28:49,029
no one came looking for me.

382
00:28:54,368 --> 00:28:57,070
[Maren] And you've been
on your own since then?

383
00:29:02,208 --> 00:29:03,276
It's not hard...

384
00:29:05,812 --> 00:29:07,647
once someone teaches you.

385
00:29:08,915 --> 00:29:09,849
[sniffs]

386
00:29:11,551 --> 00:29:13,753
But you don't...
you don't, uh...

387
00:29:14,888 --> 00:29:16,823
you don't need to be alone.

388
00:29:18,124 --> 00:29:20,827
You can bond with me
as long as you like.

389
00:29:25,366 --> 00:29:27,067
I'm looking for someone.

390
00:29:29,736 --> 00:29:30,970
Your mama.

391
00:29:32,205 --> 00:29:33,773
You mentioned
your daddy last night,

392
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:35,275
so I knew he was in the picture.

393
00:29:35,342 --> 00:29:37,043
You must be runnin' from him

394
00:29:38,011 --> 00:29:39,612
or he left you or somethin'.

395
00:29:39,679 --> 00:29:41,348
[flies buzzing]

396
00:29:41,415 --> 00:29:44,184
But you didn't say nothin'
about your mama, though.

397
00:29:46,186 --> 00:29:47,253
I never met her.

398
00:29:49,122 --> 00:29:51,791
All I have is the name of
the town she was born in.

399
00:29:51,858 --> 00:29:53,561
It's on my birth certificate.

400
00:29:53,626 --> 00:29:54,861
Mm-hmm.

401
00:29:55,795 --> 00:29:57,565
We better clean up

402
00:29:57,630 --> 00:30:00,900
before we dry stuck
to these chairs.

403
00:30:02,001 --> 00:30:03,970
- [flies continue buzzing]
- [grunts]

404
00:30:24,791 --> 00:30:30,096
[Sully singing] ♪ <i>Beautiful,
beautiful brown eyes</i>

405
00:30:30,163 --> 00:30:34,435
♪ <i>Beautiful, beautiful brown</i>

406
00:30:34,502 --> 00:30:36,769
[flies continue buzzing]

407
00:30:39,139 --> 00:30:43,310
♪ <i>Beautiful,</i>
<i>beautiful brown eyes ♪</i>

408
00:30:46,179 --> 00:30:47,981
[men chattering]

409
00:31:13,173 --> 00:31:14,941
[Maren's father]
<i>The next few, I didn't see.</i>

410
00:31:16,310 --> 00:31:18,612
<i>A boy went missin'
at a camp you went to.</i>

411
00:31:18,678 --> 00:31:20,246
<i>I shouldn't have let you go.</i>

412
00:31:21,649 --> 00:31:23,216
<i>But you wanted to.</i>

413
00:31:23,283 --> 00:31:25,352
<i>It was just a week.
You were eight.</i>

414
00:31:27,120 --> 00:31:29,390
<i>When that boy went missin',
I knew</i>

415
00:31:30,491 --> 00:31:32,992
<i>this is who you are.</i>

416
00:31:33,059 --> 00:31:34,894
<i>I never thought "what" you are.</i>

417
00:31:36,530 --> 00:31:38,898
<i>I don't know if I loved you
the way a father should,</i>

418
00:31:38,965 --> 00:31:40,800
<i>but I... I didn't hate you.</i>

419
00:31:41,701 --> 00:31:43,269
<i>You...</i>

420
00:31:43,337 --> 00:31:45,406
<i>You ate them.
I believed you had to.</i>

421
00:31:45,472 --> 00:31:46,473
<i>I don't know why.</i>

422
00:31:48,409 --> 00:31:51,412
<i>They found his pup tent
pitched in the heavy woods,</i>

423
00:31:51,478 --> 00:31:52,745
<i>all bloody inside.</i>

424
00:31:52,812 --> 00:31:55,148
<i>Luke somethin' Vanderbilt.</i>

425
00:31:55,215 --> 00:31:57,016
[driver on PA]
<i>Good evening, everyone.</i>

426
00:31:57,083 --> 00:31:58,452
[Maren's father]
<i>They ruled it a homicide,</i>

427
00:31:58,519 --> 00:32:00,153
<i>I... I never heard.</i>

428
00:32:00,220 --> 00:32:02,389
[driver] <i>This is the end</i>
<i>of the line.</i>

429
00:32:02,456 --> 00:32:04,592
[Maren's father] <i>Vanderwall</i>
<i>or somethin' like that.</i>

430
00:32:04,658 --> 00:32:06,759
[driver] <i>Take all</i>
<i>your belongings with you.</i>

431
00:32:06,826 --> 00:32:08,761
[Mare[Maren's father] <i>erwall</i>
<i>I watched after to see.</i>

432
00:32:08,828 --> 00:32:10,497
<i>If you looked sad,
and you didn't.</i>

433
00:32:10,564 --> 00:32:12,366
<i>That was the beginnin'
of sayin' no to things.</i>

434
00:32:14,167 --> 00:32:15,902
<i>Now you know why for that, too.</i>

435
00:32:36,155 --> 00:32:38,024
[music playing on speakers]

436
00:32:38,091 --> 00:32:39,826
[man] So I was thinking...

437
00:32:43,530 --> 00:32:45,231
[indistinct chatter]

438
00:32:50,036 --> 00:32:51,204
[woman] No. It's not there.

439
00:32:52,138 --> 00:32:53,507
[indistinct chatter]

440
00:33:08,722 --> 00:33:10,957
You don't have Lunchables?

441
00:33:11,024 --> 00:33:12,559
What kind of
