[Maren panting]

1011
01:09:57,163 --> 01:09:58,365
Maren, you okay?

1012
01:10:00,066 --> 01:10:01,234
What are you doing?

1013
01:10:04,905 --> 01:10:07,273
What? Oh, Christ.

1014
01:10:07,341 --> 01:10:09,008
Okay, we didn't know.

1015
01:10:10,176 --> 01:10:12,211
Hey, we didn't know,
okay? [tuts]

1016
01:10:18,284 --> 01:10:20,019
[woman 1] Is he back?

1017
01:10:20,086 --> 01:10:21,889
[woman 2] No!
Something's wrong, Mom!

1018
01:10:21,955 --> 01:10:23,590
All right, we gotta go.
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

1019
01:10:23,657 --> 01:10:24,791
Focus, focus.
Come on, let's go.

1020
01:10:43,644 --> 01:10:47,581
[radio host] <i>Only there</i>
<i>did civilization arise.</i>

1021
01:10:47,648 --> 01:10:50,651
<i>Now, it's not my intention
to give a history lesson,</i>

1022
01:10:50,717 --> 01:10:53,286
<i>but I believe it's important
to remind ourselves</i>

1023
01:10:53,353 --> 01:10:55,187
<i>that in dealing
with the economy,</i>

1024
01:10:55,254 --> 01:10:57,089
<i>we're dealing with
human creativity.</i>

1025
01:10:58,124 --> 01:10:59,826
<i>This insight has represented</i>

1026
01:10:59,893 --> 01:11:01,628
<i>the underpinning of
our economic expansion.</i>

1027
01:11:02,963 --> 01:11:04,364
There wasn't a car seat, Maren.

1028
01:11:05,499 --> 01:11:06,767
He wasn't wearing
a wedding ring.

1029
01:11:09,201 --> 01:11:10,537
We should feel something.

1030
01:11:11,338 --> 01:11:13,139
'Cause we murder people.

1031
01:11:13,205 --> 01:11:14,741
We steal their stuff,
we move the fuck on,

1032
01:11:14,808 --> 01:11:16,710
and we ruin lives
that we don't even see.

1033
01:11:16,777 --> 01:11:18,345
Come on, why are we talking
about it like this?

1034
01:11:18,412 --> 01:11:19,780
We gotta do this!
We have to do it!

1035
01:11:20,647 --> 01:11:22,214
[sniffles]

1036
01:11:22,281 --> 01:11:24,283
[Maren]
Talking about the future,

1037
01:11:24,351 --> 01:11:26,587
talking about being
a friend to yourself.

1038
01:11:26,653 --> 01:11:29,690
You don't have that.
This is too much.

1039
01:11:31,223 --> 01:11:35,696
No, we got 60, 70 years of this?

1040
01:11:39,165 --> 01:11:40,667
How dare you make this harder.

1041
01:11:49,977 --> 01:11:51,812
Maren, what do I...
What am I supposed...

1042
01:11:53,013 --> 01:11:54,448
How do I get you out of this?

1043
01:11:54,514 --> 01:11:55,649
What am I supposed to say
right now?

1044
01:11:57,050 --> 01:11:58,284
Just drive.

1045
01:11:59,019 --> 01:12:01,355
Right. All right.

1046
01:12:13,500 --> 01:12:15,669
[Maren breathing heavily]

1047
01:12:20,540 --> 01:12:21,708
[gasping]

1048
01:12:24,411 --> 01:12:27,146
[Lee] You were dreaming.
We're almost there.

1049
01:12:28,815 --> 01:12:29,883
[chuckles]

1050
01:12:34,253 --> 01:12:35,856
[patrons chattering]

1051
01:12:38,091 --> 01:12:41,762
Uh, do have a telephone book?
The one outside's missing.

1052
01:12:42,562 --> 01:12:43,830
Uh...

1053
01:12:43,897 --> 01:12:45,599
I'm looking for someone
in Bagley.

1054
01:12:45,666 --> 01:12:47,934
Oh. This is for
the county, sweetie.

1055
01:12:56,410 --> 01:12:57,944
[breathing heavily]

1056
01:12:59,479 --> 01:13:00,947
[Maren] Thanks.

1057
01:13:04,216 --> 01:13:05,352
There.

1058
01:13:14,695 --> 01:13:16,963
- I'll come with you.
- No, stay here.

1059
01:13:29,409 --> 01:13:31,712
Excuse me?
Are you Barbara Kerns?

1060
01:13:40,252 --> 01:13:42,422
Wait, wait. Ms. Kerns.
Ms. Kerns.

1061
01:13:43,156 --> 01:13:44,357
I'm Maren Yearly.

1062
01:13:44,958 --> 01:13:46,660
Maren.

1063
01:13:46,727 --> 01:13:48,695
I've traveled a very long way.

1064
01:13:57,370 --> 01:13:59,072
Oh, they didn't marry.

1065
01:13:59,139 --> 01:14:00,707
Hmm. Yeah, we wondered.

1066
01:14:01,273 --> 01:14:02,409
Huh.

1067
01:14:03,810 --> 01:14:07,981
My husband, uh,
he died years ago.

1068
01:14:08,048 --> 01:14:09,516
Throat cancer.

1069
01:14:09,583 --> 01:14:11,818
- Sorry.
- Mm.

1070
01:14:11,885 --> 01:14:13,954
Sorry to surprise you like this.

1071
01:14:15,756 --> 01:14:18,692
You didn't know your daughter
had a child, I guess.

1072
01:14:19,659 --> 01:14:20,994
No.

1073
01:14:21,061 --> 01:14:23,897
No. When she wanted
to get married,

1074
01:14:24,798 --> 01:14:25,732
we didn't agree.

1075
01:14:26,700 --> 01:14:29,836
So, it drove her away. Yeah.

1076
01:14:32,572 --> 01:14:34,608
Where did she meet my dad?

1077
01:14:36,209 --> 01:14:37,410
He didn't say?

1078
01:14:38,645 --> 01:14:40,714
He wouldn't say
anything about her.

1079
01:14:41,982 --> 01:14:42,916
Ah.

1080
01:14:43,884 --> 01:14:45,852
Hmm. Mm.

1081
01:14:47,954 --> 01:14:48,922
[sighs]

1082
01:14:57,364 --> 01:15:00,500
They met in college.
Down in Mankato.

1083
01:15:01,434 --> 01:15:02,903
She finished two years

1084
01:15:02,969 --> 01:15:04,538
before he talked her
into leaving.

1085
01:15:05,939 --> 01:15:08,408
Did he drive you here?
Is he outside?

1086
01:15:08,475 --> 01:15:10,944
No. He's in Maryland.

1087
01:15:14,447 --> 01:15:16,416
Does he know you're here?

1088
01:15:16,483 --> 01:15:18,351
Yeah, he let me know
where to find you.

1089
01:15:19,286 --> 01:15:20,787
So you haven't run away?

1090
01:15:21,354 --> 01:15:22,422
No.

1091
01:15:22,489 --> 01:15:23,924
My dad thinks that

1092
01:15:23,990 --> 01:15:25,492
I'm old enough
to live on my own.

1093
01:15:25,559 --> 01:15:27,494
Oh. Uh-huh.

1094
01:15:27,561 --> 01:15:30,530
Well, if you're looking for
a home with your mother,

1095
01:15:31,798 --> 01:15:32,766
um,

1096
01:15:33,633 --> 01:15:35,468
I'm sorry to tell you

1097
01:15:35,535 --> 01:15:38,071
that she...
she's no longer with us.

1098
01:15:41,074 --> 01:15:42,576
What? When?

1099
01:15:42,642 --> 01:15:44,344
It's a lot of years now,

1100
01:15:44,411 --> 01:15:46,580
and it's nothing
I wanna tell you about.

1101
01:15:46,646 --> 01:15:48,148
I hope you can respect that.

1102
01:15:48,215 --> 01:15:49,549
Well, I'm her daughter.

1103
01:15:50,550 --> 01:15:52,385
Yep. Makes sense now.

1104
01:15:52,452 --> 01:15:56,723
Why she came back so bereaved.
That's the word.

1105
01:15:57,924 --> 01:16:00,026
And she wouldn't tell us
anything, either.

1106
01:16:01,561 --> 01:16:05,432
Oh, it's just so much hiding
in one family.

1107
01:16:06,800 --> 01:16:09,135
I'm sorry you had to be
the child of it all.

1108
01:16:11,538 --> 01:16:13,807
Wait. What was
she like as a child?

1109
01:16:16,243 --> 01:16:17,444
Hmm.

1110
01:16:23,483 --> 01:16:25,485
Wow. She was your only child?

1111
01:16:25,552 --> 01:16:27,187
[Barbara] Well, not even ours.

1112
01:16:27,254 --> 01:16:30,056
Bob and I never could have
babies of our own.

1113
01:16:31,359 --> 01:16:33,093
But then we heard about Janelle.

1114
01:16:34,160 --> 01:16:35,595
She'd been left behind

1115
01:16:35,662 --> 01:16:37,964
a sheriff's station in Bemidji.

1116
01:16:38,031 --> 01:16:39,666
It was in the paper.

1117
01:16:39,733 --> 01:16:42,402
You know anything
about her biological parents?

1118
01:16:42,469 --> 01:16:43,937
No, nothing.

1119
01:16:44,004 --> 01:16:45,739
Except what they did
to their baby.

1120
01:16:45,805 --> 01:16:48,408
I mean, she could have froze,
you know.

1121
01:16:48,475 --> 01:16:50,443
It's cold here all the time.

1122
01:16:52,545 --> 01:16:54,348
My mother...

1123
01:16:54,414 --> 01:16:56,650
You can, you know, take those
photos if you want 'em.

1124
01:16:56,716 --> 01:16:58,151
Did she ever hurt anyone?

1125
01:16:59,753 --> 01:17:01,588
What kind of question is that?

1126
01:17:02,889 --> 01:17:06,559
I bet she did. I know she did.

1127
01:17:06,626 --> 01:17:08,495
I don't know what you had
to do to cover it up

1128
01:17:08,561 --> 01:17:11,064
or... how much pain
it caused you.

1129
01:17:11,131 --> 01:17:12,799
Stop this. At once.

1130
01:17:12,866 --> 01:17:15,168
Look, you're never
going to see me again, okay?

1131
01:17:15,235 --> 01:17:18,738
You may not be her family
by blood, but I am.

1132
01:17:18,805 --> 01:17:20,408
And I need to know.

1133
01:17:20,473 --> 01:17:22,709
So, please, Mrs. Kerns,
please...

1134
01:17:22,776 --> 01:17:24,611
Then ask her yourself.

1135
01:17:28,114 --> 01:17:29,082
How?

1136
01:17:31,918 --> 01:17:32,852
[sighs]

1137
01:17:33,753 --> 01:17:36,122
Look, I don't know you.

1138
01:17:36,189 --> 01:17:37,857
You gotta understand.

1139
01:17:37,924 --> 01:17:39,659
I didn't know what you wanted
comin' up here.

1140
01:17:39,726 --> 01:17:41,194
And I hope you mean what you say

1141
01:17:41,261 --> 01:17:43,096
about never coming back here.

1142
01:17:43,163 --> 01:17:47,934
I know that sounds cold,
but I wanna be clear with ya.

1143
01:17:48,001 --> 01:17:50,303
I told you she was
no longer with us,

1144
01:17:50,371 --> 01:17:52,939
but she's not...
she's not dead.

1145
01:17:54,741 --> 01:17:58,144
She's living in a town
called Fergus Falls.

1146
01:17:59,279 --> 01:18:00,513
In a state hospital there.

1147
01:18:00,580 --> 01:18:02,549
And we didn't put her there,

1148
01:18:02,615 --> 01:18:04,284
if that's what you're thinkin'.

1149
01:18:04,352 --> 01:18:06,320
She signed her own papers.

1150
01:18:06,387 --> 01:18:07,520
[door opens]

1151
01:18:09,289 --> 01:18:10,490
[door closes]

1152
01:18:18,765 --> 01:18:20,166
[panting] Okay.

1153
01:18:29,809 --> 01:18:32,846
Here. My mother's here.

1154
01:19:13,487 --> 01:19:14,621
Do you want me to come in?

1155
01:19:15,356 --> 01:19:16,289
No.

1156
01:19:38,546 --> 01:19:40,414
[nurse] Mrs. Kerns' daughter.

1157
01:19:40,481 --> 01:19:43,883
I sure didn't expect this
when I woke up this morning.

1158
01:19:45,486 --> 01:19:46,986
[muffled shouting]

1159
01:19:48,254 --> 01:19:49,523
[woman screaming]

1160
01:19:49,589 --> 01:19:51,057
[woman 2] Calm down.

1161
01:19:53,427 --> 01:19:54,661
Calm down.

1162
01:19:55,396 --> 01:19:57,331
Is she dangerous?

1163
01:19:57,398 --> 01:20:00,066
It's been many years
since that was a concern.

1164
01:20:00,133 --> 01:20:01,968
[woman 3 crying]

1165
01:20:03,703 --> 01:20:05,271
Why was it ever one?

1166
01:20:05,339 --> 01:20:08,309
Aggression towards the staff.
Self-harm.

1167
01:20:09,310 --> 01:20:10,710
But long ago.

1168
01:20:12,612 --> 01:20:14,348
[keys jingling]

1169
01:20:14,415 --> 01:20:17,117
It's possible she won't
understand who you are.

1170
01:20:18,218 --> 01:20:19,619
She just took her morning meds,

1171
01:20:19,686 --> 01:20:21,621
so she may nod off anyhow.

1172
01:20:22,288 --> 01:20:23,890
We'll see.

1173
01:20:23,957 --> 01:20:26,025
There's someone here
to see you, Ms. Kerns.

1174
01:20:26,092 --> 01:20:29,229
A surprise.
A wonderful surprise.

1175
01:20:54,488 --> 01:20:55,655
[Maren] It's Maren.

1176
01:20:57,391 --> 01:20:58,325
I'm Maren.

1177
01:21:03,597 --> 01:21:04,697
Can't she speak?

1178
01:21:04,764 --> 01:21:05,999
It's the medication.

1179
01:21:07,535 --> 01:21:10,069
[whimpers, breathing shakily]

1180
01:21:10,136 --> 01:21:11,938
Easy, Ms. Kerns.

1181
01:21:16,075 --> 01:21:17,911
I didn't come with Dad.

1182
01:21:19,513 --> 01:21:22,682
I didn't come with Dad.
Just came by myself.

1183
01:21:24,951 --> 01:21:26,387
Should I give her
the letter, Ms. Kerns?

1184
01:21:26,453 --> 01:21:27,687
I fetched it on the way up.

1185
01:21:27,754 --> 01:21:29,956
[whimpering]

1186
01:21:34,361 --> 01:21:38,131
She wrote this about
15 years ago now, must be.

1187
01:21:38,198 --> 01:21:41,901
I've kept it safe in her file
out there, in case.

1188
01:21:48,708 --> 01:21:49,943
She knew I'd come?

1189
01:21:51,645 --> 01:21:53,012
I'll wait right over here.

1190
01:22:05,626 --> 01:22:10,964
[Janelle] <i>Maren, if a day comes</i>
<i>when you show up here,</i>

1191
01:22:11,030 --> 01:22:15,034
<i>I'll know it's because
your father broke his promise.</i>

1192
01:22:16,069 --> 01:22:17,971
<i>Told you something about me.</i>

1193
01:22:19,072 --> 01:22:20,273
<i>And I'll know why.</i>

1194
01:22:21,941 --> 01:22:24,244
<i>He didn't know what I was
when we married,</i>

1195
01:22:24,311 --> 01:22:28,214
<i>but he figured it out
by the time I had you.</i>

1196
01:22:28,281 --> 01:22:31,518
<i>I promised I would never hurt
either of you,</i>

1197
01:22:31,585 --> 01:22:34,588
<i>but how could we be sure?</i>

1198
01:22:34,655 --> 01:22:38,659
<i>It wasn't easy to leave.
I loved you both so much.</i>

1199
01:22:38,726 --> 01:22:40,527
<i>I thought about ending my life,</i>

1200
01:22:40,594 --> 01:22:45,399
<i>but I wanted to be here
in case you ever did come.</i>

1201
01:22:47,000 --> 01:22:50,036
<i>All I ever wanted
in this world was love.</i>

1202
01:22:50,103 --> 01:22:52,740
<i>I tried, believed,</i>

1203
01:22:52,805 --> 01:22:55,074
<i>but we can't have it as we are.</i>

1204
01:22:55,141 --> 01:22:57,478
<i>All we can have
is a little space,</i>

1205
01:22:57,544 --> 01:23:01,715
<i>with bars or a door that locks.</i>

1206
01:23:01,781 --> 01:23:05,151
[tearfully] <i>I'm sorry</i>
<i>for that, Little Yearly.</i>

1207
01:23:06,553 --> 01:23:09,222
<i>For all the things
I didn't do for you</i>

1208
01:23:09,289 --> 01:23:13,360
<i>and for the one thing
I still can.</i>

1209
01:23:14,428 --> 01:23:16,162
<i>The world of love</i>

1210
01:23:16,229 --> 01:23:18,332
<i>- wants no monsters in it.</i>
- [breathing heavily]

1211
01:23:23,202 --> 01:23:25,171
<i>So let me help you out of it.</i>

1212
01:23:25,238 --> 01:23:27,574
- [growling]
- [Maren gasping]

1213
01:23:31,412 --> 01:23:32,579
[Maren] No! Help me!

1214
01:23:32,646 --> 01:23:34,581
Ms. Kerns, calm down!

1215
01:23:35,449 --> 01:23:37,318
Maren, die.

1216
01:23:38,951 --> 01:23:40,253
[Maren] Let me out. Let me out.

1217
01:23:40,321 --> 01:23:41,988
Press the button
on the door. Go!

1218
01:23:43,757 --> 01:23:45,258
[gasping]

1219
01:23:45,326 --> 01:23:47,960
[blubbering]

1220
01:23:51,799 --> 01:23:53,166
[door rattling]

1221
01:23:54,535 --> 01:23:56,403
I can't open the door.
I can't open the door.

1222
01:23:56,470 --> 01:23:58,204
[Lee] Sorry, sorry.
Here we go, here we go.

1223
01:23:58,271 --> 01:24:00,106
[Maren] I can't
fucking with the door.

1224
01:24:00,173 --> 01:24:01,575
[Lee] You're good.

1225
01:24:01,642 --> 01:24:03,344
[Maren] She's one of us.

1226
01:24:03,410 --> 01:24:04,944
She's one of us
but she's fucking nuts.

1227
01:24:05,011 --> 01:24:06,814
She ate her own fucking hands.

1228
01:24:06,879 --> 01:24:08,315
She said she loved my dad.

1229
01:24:08,382 --> 01:24:09,583
She said she wanted to be a mom.

1230
01:24:10,617 --> 01:24:12,251
She could have stayed.

1231
01:24:12,319 --> 01:24:14,187
She could have told me
what I needed to know.

1232
01:24:14,253 --> 01:24:16,222
But all of this...
Fuck, you know how different

1233
01:24:16,289 --> 01:24:18,091
this would've been if I'd had
one person on my side?

1234
01:24:18,157 --> 01:24:20,226
One person to talk to?

1235
01:24:20,293 --> 01:24:22,195
You know what
I wouldn't have done?

1236
01:24:22,261 --> 01:24:24,365
Maybe, probably half
of what I've fucking done!

1237
01:24:25,131 --> 01:24:26,767
Fuck her. Fuck.

1238
01:24:26,834 --> 01:24:28,167
[Lee] You know, if she'd stayed,

1239
01:24:28,234 --> 01:24:30,103
she might have hurt you, Maren.

1240
01:24:30,169 --> 01:24:32,539
Or worse, you might not even
be here right now.

1241
01:24:32,606 --> 01:24:34,375
Trust me, I know what I'm
talking about with this stuff.

1242
01:24:34,441 --> 01:24:36,142
This is better than
what I went through.

1243
01:24:36,209 --> 01:24:38,177
Please just stop
fucking talking!

1244
01:24:39,879 --> 01:24:41,881
You're pissed off, and you're
scared, and you feel alone,

1245
01:24:41,948 --> 01:24:44,183
and you don't know what to do
with it all, it's fine.

1246
01:24:44,250 --> 01:24:45,652
If you wanna go at yourself
with that, I can't stop you.

1247
01:24:46,720 --> 01:24:47,654
But don't come at me.

1248
01:24:48,689 --> 01:24:50,858
You slit his throat, Lee.

1249
01:24:50,923 --> 01:24:53,192
- He had a wife. Kids.
- Okay.

1250
01:24:53,259 --> 01:24:55,429
I think you got used
to being locked up

1251
01:24:55,496 --> 01:24:57,263
and invisible and alone, and
now you're out in the world...

1252
01:24:57,331 --> 01:24:59,232
- Okay, okay.
- ...and you're seeing yourself

1253
01:24:59,298 --> 01:25:01,200
for the first time,
and that's freaking you out.

1254
01:25:01,267 --> 01:25:03,437
But you know what?
It's fucking me up too, okay?

1255
01:25:03,504 --> 01:25:04,904
I feel like I'm seeing myself
